mode
to
a
political
stance
that
suggests
he
might
know
something
about
running
this
big
,
troubled
city
.
###
And
now
,
at
the
crucial
moment
,
he
's
running
out
of
money
.
###
This
is
the
nation
's
biggest
city
and
,
,
its
mayor
is
the
nation
's
best-known
urban
politician
.
###
Democrats
hoped
that
Mr.
Dinkins
could
become
a
highly
visible
national
leader
.
###
Republicans
figured
that
in
Mr.
Giuliani
,
the
nation
's
best-known
prosecutor
,
they
had
a
chance
for
a
huge
upset
in
the
heart
of
Democratic
territory
and
that
they
would
pick
